olive oil
1 packet pine nuts
1 bag green beans
½ pear
1 bag mint
1 bag spinach & rocket mix
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese
1 drizzle balsamic glaze

• Heat a medium frying pan over medium-high heat. Toast pine nuts tossing,
until golden, 3-4 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• Trim green beans.
• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook
green beans, tossing, until just tender, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a plate.

• While the green beans are cooking, thinly slice pear (see ingredients).
Pick and thinly slice mint.

• In a large bowl, add a drizzle of olive oil and a generous pinch of salt and
pepper. Add spinach & rocket mix, pear, green beans, grated Parmesan
cheese and mint. Toss to coat.

TIP: Make the dressing in a serving bowl to save on washing up!

• Transfer green beans and pear salad to a serving dish.
• Sprinkle with toasted pine nuts and drizzle with some balsamic glaze to
serve. Enjoy!